STRATEGIC REASONING: {'Maximizing my utility under 3288 effort, I solved a near-knapsack: very high bang-for-effort items for me are C55 (41), A67 (75), C10 (129), A18 (118), plus strong midweights A43 (417), B42 (390), B36 (350), and heavier but still worthwhile C61 (630) and C42 (801). With these nine, I had 337 effort left; the best add within that is C08 (329) rather than C43 (151) due to higher value to me. Total effort 3280, leaving a small buffer. I intentionally excluded heavy/low-return-for-me items like A62 (887), B19 (808), C73 (849), and also C67 (602) unless there’s a strong counter-preference from the other side. My plan: anchor with this high-utility set but signal flexibility on small swaps (e.g., C08 <-> C43) and, if they insist on a heavy item, push to remove something I value less (preferably C08 first, then B36) while avoiding cuts to A67/C55/C10/A18/A43/B42. If they counter with a very heavy item like C73/B19, I’ll argue effort-efficiency and propose compensating drops that minimize my loss or suggest alternative lighter items.'}
PROPOSAL: {'C55', 'A67', 'C10', 'A18', 'A43', 'B42', 'B36', 'C61', 'C42', 'C08'}
ARGUMENT: {'This set is balanced and efficient on effort (total 3280 ≤ 3288) while keeping many low-effort, broadly useful items. I avoided the heaviest items so we have more room for multiple priorities rather than a single costly one. If you need a tweak, I can consider small swaps—e.g., C08 ↔ C43—or discuss which heavier item you’d want added and what we could remove to stay within the limit. Which items are must-haves for you?'}

STRATEGIC REASONING: {'Their proposal already includes all of my top-value items (A43, A67, C10, B42, C42, C61, C55, A18, B36) and only one low-value item for me (C08). Total effort is 3280, leaving only 8 slack, so no additional item can be added. I tested swaps: adding C67 (602) or C73 (849) would force dropping combinations that reduce my total value (e.g., dropping C61 or B36+C08 still results in net losses). Swapping C08→C43 also lowers my value. This proposal gives me 6395 total importance, and every feasible swap I checked is worse. Best move is to accept immediately.'}
ARGUMENT: {'This set covers my core priorities while staying just under the limit, and I don’t see a feasible swap that would improve things without cutting multiple useful items. I’m ready to lock this in.'}
AGREE: {'C55', 'A67', 'C10', 'A18', 'A43', 'B42', 'B36', 'C61', 'C42', 'C08'}
